body:
Running the extract -map example 1 from the February 2016 tutorial slides (slide 96) causes outputs to appear as inputs (below). The example is supposed to map a multiply-accumulate operation, but the outputs are flipped when run on the current version of yosys. I am not sure if this is a bug inside of the show command, or due to an underlying issue in extract.

![bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5099107/15001854/fd644db2-114f-11e6-9303-34908f978668.png)

Inputs are as listed:

```
/*macc_simple_test.v*/
module test(a, b, c, d, y);  
input [15:0] a, b;
input [31:0] c, d;
output [31:0] y;
assign
y = a*b + c + d;
endmodule

/*macc_simple_xmap.v*/
module macc_16_16_32(a, b, c, y); 
input [15:0] a, b;
input [31:0] c;
output [31:0] y;
assign y = a*b + c;
endmodule

# Yosys script
read_verilog macc_simple_test.v 
hierarchy -check -top test
extract -map macc_simple_xmap.v;;
show
```

